HEADWORD: Trilling
<hw>Tril"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>drilling</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One of tree children born
at the same birth.</def> <rj><au>Wright.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>A compound crystal,
consisting of three individuals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trillion</ent>⟦br⟧
